      "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/forums.trainerday.com/alex/{size}/1331_2.png",
      "created_at": "2021-03-01T08:53:19.216Z",
      "cooked": "<p>I realized also a better solution for a ramp test with fixed watts AT THIS TIME is doing it like this.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Set your FTP correctly (or close, for example instead of 196 maybe 200) in our web app</li>\n<li>Create a ramp test based on specific watts and save it as Ramp Test 200W</li>\n<li>Load that in the web app and always set your FTP to 200W before the test</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Even when your FTP improves it will be accurately reflected. Eventually when you get to a higher level like 210W create a new ramp test for 210w.</p>",
      "post_number": 5,
      "post_type": 1,
      "updated_at": "2021-03-01T08:53:36.356Z",
